 BARBERTON – Mthembu was among the lucky people to watch the UEFA Champions League final last Saturday at Wanda Metropolitano Stadium in Madrid. Read More: Barberton sportcaster jet off to Spain Liverpool, a team Mthembu was supporting in the final, beat Tottenham Hotspurs 2-0 to win the trophy. Mthembu say he thoroughly enjoyed the tour. He, along with other winners and delegation from MTN South Africa jetted out of the country last week Wednesday. They returned into the country on Wednesday. “The tour was a dream come true. To be among the 68 000 soccer fans at the stadium was like a dream. I thoroughly enjoyed the tour. I learned a lot,” said Mthembu. Mthembu won the trip after being chosen as the MTN 8 Last Journalist Standing (LJS). 